modules.description: This module enables command-line argument parsing by supporting mandatory, optional, and repeated parameters of diverse types (strings, integers, floats, enums, and custom formats), along with flags, subcommands, and structured section organization. It processes string lists representing user input, leverages customizable type parsers for domain-specific needs, and generates contextual help documentation. Typical applications include building CLI tools requiring robust input validation, hierarchical command structures (e.g., git-style workflows), and automated usage guidance.
